54.9	Thompson_submachine_gun	Thompson submachine gun	The Thompson is an American submachine gun, invented by John T. Thompson in 1919, that became infamous during the Prohibition era. It was a common sight in the media of the time, being used by both law enforcement officers and criminals. The Thompson was also known informally as: the "Tommy Gun", "Trench Broom", "Trench Sweeper", "Chicago Typewriter", "Chicago Piano", "Chicago Style", and "The Chopper".	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f4/Submachine_gun_M1928_Thompson.jpg/300px-Submachine_gun_M1928_Thompson.jpg
